text.paragraph:
Nonselective monoamine oxidase (MAO) inhibitors are contraindicated for use with carbidopa and levodopa extended-release. These inhibitors must be discontinued at least two weeks prior to initiating therapy with carbidopa and levodopa extended-release. Carbidopa and levodopa extended-release may be administered concomitantly with the manufacturer's recommended dose of an MAO inhibitor with selectivity for MAO type B (e.g., selegiline HCl) (see


                        PRECAUTIONS, Drug Interactions
                     ).

Carbidopa and levodopa extended-release should be substituted at a dosage that will provide approximately 25% of the previous levodopa dosage (see


                        DOSAGE AND ADMINISTRATION
                     ).

Skin:  Malignant melanoma (see also


   CONTRAINDICATIONS
), increased sweating.
